subject: p13881772
Findings: Frontal radiograph of the chest demonstrates stable mild enlargement of the cardiac silhouette. Normal mediastinal and hilar contours. Compared to the prior study of the bilateral pleural effusions have resolved. No focal consolidation or pneumothorax present. No pulmonary edema. The lungs remain hyperinflated.
